column5: How about here, huh? Bill Krejca

right on the highway going through Emo there is a good place to eat, nothing fancy, but its good.I cant remember the name though???The Emo Inn (also on the highway) has good food as welledit. It's called Circle D
Somebody new bought that rest. in Emo and fixed it up a bit. I've only eaten breakfast there and it's pretty good and reasonable.

Yeppers, I live just down the road and we eat there a few times per month. Breaky is good, but so are the lunches and suppers. Again, it's nothing fancy, but the servings are good, the food is good and its pretty cheap. There is also a place called CanAsian about a half block down too, but its not my cup of tea.
Are we talking about "Circle D" or "the other one?" Thanks. Bill

Circle D is where you wanna eat, sorry for any confusion, lol.Any plans to hit up rainy river while your down???http://i1201.photobucket.com/albums/...oodporn008.jpgor stop by for a coffee and some fish talk, lol
wow, that photo just made me extremely hungry

Good looking food! We probably will stop for breakfast at Circle D on the 17th. Be happy to have you join us. Not sure on time, have to pick up a few groceries, cross the RR border, and then drive over. Email me at [email protected] if interested. Bill

It was very nice to meet you and your crappie fishing team Bill! lol Hope you enjoyed breaky and some fishing talk at Circle D, and I never said thanks for grabbing my coffee, so thanks! Hope you guys have a great trip, look forward to hearing about those slabs!!!
